The '''crimson-winged woodpecker''' ('''''Picus puniceus''''') is a species of bird in the [[woodpecker]] family. It is found in [[Brunei]], [[Indonesia]], [[Malaysia]], [[Myanmar]], [[Singapore]], and [[Thailand]]. Its natural [[habitat]] is subtropical or tropical moist lowland [[forest]]s. It can grow up to 25&nbsp;cm long. Its diet is mainly insects and larvae. It is a bright and colourful bird that is hard to misidentify.

